{
  "texts": [
    "Informativeness-based approaches are considered as the best strategy in Active Learning and they can be categorized into bayesian 16 and non-bayesian 23 frameworks.",
    "The bayesian approach, such as the one proposed by Gal et al.",
    "16, uses Monte Carlo Dropout to estimate the uncertainty of the unlabeled data.",
    "However, this method requires dense dropout layers, which can reduce the convergence speed and result in huge computational costs for large-scale learning.",
    "In contrast, non-Bayesian frameworks like the one proposed by Li et al."
  ]
}